reviews.text: chinese food and the setting at this spot is excellent. Service is always timely even when they have a full house. The place has a great feel to it. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I loved.
Great food no matter what time your there, friendly staff all on top of things
A favorite location for chinese food. looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. the bill was good for how much you get.
Loved it... Food & service was awesome
Good food, good prices... What more needs to be said

The food here is spectacular, and the owner is a first-rate human being.  I love their gyros, but if you're not a fan of lamb or chicken, try the Philly cheese steak gyro -- fantastic!
The only negative is that they need more servers, so when they get busy, the service degrades (as one would expect).   They also have trouble getting my order right; it comes out wrong almost every time, though it is admittedly a highly customized order.
Despite those minor inconveniences, we love coming here, and we do so as often as we can.  Highly recommended!

This is some of the worst service I’ve ever recieved. Not only did the waiters/waitresses have no idea how to explain the menu, the wait was awful and we ended up having to hand-deliver our payment to the kitchen because we waited for over 15 minutes (last customers there) and nobody came to pick it up. My Gyro was alright, my friend’s Beef Marga was slightly above average. The saving graces here were the delicious Turkish coffee and side salad that came with my gyro lol.
One of the few places in town to get ethnic food. Casual dining serving gyros, lamb, falafel, hummus, dolmas, pitas, etc.
Food was good, service quick, though the place could use some more decoration.

The food can be hit or miss in quality.  I live the plate that is a combination of hummus and other things, (can't remember the name ).  The ambiance leaves a lot to be desired.  But it is Mediterranean food in Los Alamos,  and I'm glad they're there.

Loved the choices of sauce #5 being our favorite. Had better meat. Didn't care for the cashier at all but the bus guy was fabulous with our daughter. From Indiana if ever in the area it is worth the trip.

The food absolutely delicious. I went there for dinner. The atmosphere is nice and casual. They have all the classics but i had chicken this time. The meat was flavorful and tender and marinated well. The sides are equally great. I had ordered cheesy corn which was fantastic. They had a party going on next door but it wasn't crazy crowded. Great place for some delicious bbq.
Really good food. The diner has a bit of a cafeteria feel. Large portions, and super tasty!

This is the second time that I have been to this place and ended up dissatisfied. The first time I was ill. I suspected it was my barbecue. It was confirmed when a friend ate my leftovers and became sick. That was around 5 years ago. I visited recently, and the barbecue on my sandwich tasted old. It was three of us lunching. One person took her food back, for different reasons(I didn't bother to) which had the same meat. They remade her food and the same meat had a different color... Like it was fresh, not dark with that reheated look and taste to it. I keep hearing good things about this place, so maybe one day I will try them and they will be on point. But until then I will stick to 3 stars. The staff was nice, and the food was fast and hot... But let's work on the fresh.
Best bbq in town.  Good selection of sauces.  Had a special of burnt ends today which are outstanding.  The potato salad is excellent.

I love this place with all my heart and soul. The food is always amazing as well as the employees. There is only one problem and it is that my order is always wrong. Call or order in person I am always missing something/given one order wrong, given less of what I've ordered, or getting extremely spicy food when I asked for it not to be spicy. I've spent close to or over $1,000 here and I've given up on believing my order is correct, but the food is too good not to come back. If I have to check my food visually and taste test it every time I'll gladly do it, I just wish I didn't have to.

The food and staff are great and friendly. Whenever I come here with my partner we tend to get a party platter, you get a little bit of a lot of things and it always fills us up. It's great if you are looking for a variety of items but don't want to order too much.

We were invited by our friend to have dinner. Food was horrible. Waiters they don't know what they were serving. They need more crew. They even missed the order. we ordered lamb curry, Thali, chicken tikka masala.
I will not recommend ruin our trip all the way from Santa Rosa.

this is my current favourite Indian restaurant. the dinner menu has a good selection, and the food is great. they also have a wider array of naan-like options than any other place i have tried. the parking lot is cramped and can be difficult to navigate.
The food is fresh and plentiful. The restaurant is easy to get to. The food is good.
